==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jacksnipe
<hw>Jack"snipe`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A small European snipe (<spn>Limnocryptes
gallinula</spn>); -- called also <altname>judcock</altname>,
<altname>jedcock</altname>, <altname>juddock</altname>,
<altname>jed</altname>, and <altname>half snipe</altname>.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A small American sandpiper (<spn>Tringa
maculata</spn>); -- called also <altname>pectoral sandpiper</altname>,
and <altname>grass snipe</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jackstay</ent>⟦br⟧
